
 * VS 2013 Update 1 comes with a built in Git client
 * It works in any directory with a .git folder
 * In VS, go to View > Team Explorer
 * The Connect Window has a Local Git Repositories section
 ** the list contains previously opened local git repos
 ** add lets you add a local repo
 ** clicking a repo shows its detail view
 ** changes is the view when writing code
 ** unsynced commits & branches is for pulling/merging
